			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Load up CTY_Main_A&#xD;&#xA;open the debug book and set the prisoners to saved&#xD;&#xA;Open ReCon and use &quot;oe low_foundry_fundangofollower&quot;&#xD;&#xA;also set up &quot;Roll horrible&quot;&#xD;&#xA;teleport to -1982; -1; 420 and pick a fight with nearby enemies. Start killing them until a killswitch drops.&#xD;&#xA;Attempt to disarm one - because of roll horrilbe it will fail&#xD;&#xA;observe the consequences&#xD;&#xA;Finish the fight&#xD;&#xA;the dialog should auto-start" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="49" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="This dialog covers an edge case: the player has freed Iron throne prisoners, returned to the foundry and recruited Toobin as a follower. On the way to the control centre a kill switch accidentally goes off, killing all the gondians.&#xD;&#xA;Because of this Toobin is ready to give up. The player may attempt to persuade him to keep going." />
